+/// TC-33 fix-1 — the inclusive epoch-seconds range SQLite's
+/// `strftime(..., 'unixepoch')` can render back to ISO-8601. SQLite's date
+/// functions cover years 0000..=9999 ONLY, so:
+/// - `MIN` = `0000-01-01T00:00:00Z`
